    _ THE SECOND PART OF Geodetia, containing the measuring of the superficiall content or Area of any platte, peece of ground, mappe or such like, howsoeuer formed: and that two kinde of waies, as Arithmeticall, or vulgarly without calculation, with diuerse new tables, as well for the casting vp or deuiding of grounds, as also to extract the square roote, or finde the true square of any number, with the measuring of all kinde of superficies, as boords, glasse, &c. or solids, as tymber, stone, &c. after diuerse waies, both old & new, together with the ground of the worke: also to seeke dimensions of heights, bredths, &c. by protracting after my new kinde of working, to separate or inclose grounds, or make any figure according vnto any proportion assigned onely by the staffe, to metamorphize or transforme any figure from one shape vnto any other, for the more speede in measuring to finde what proportion peeces of ground, glasse, boords, or any superficies one hath to the other: the making of a compendious Table to containe the legall part of measuring ground, with many Apophthegmes, requisite for all Geodetors to vnderstand.

    _ THE SECOND PART OF Geodetia, containing the measuring of the superficiall content or Area of any platte, peece of ground, mappe or such like, howsoeuer formed: and that two kinde of waies, as Arithmeticall, or vulgarly without calculation, with diuerse new tables, as well for the casting vp or deuiding of grounds, as also to extract the square roote, or finde the true square of any number, with the measuring of all kinde of superficies, as boords, glasse, &c. or solids, as tymber, stone, &c. after diuerse waies, both old & new, together with the ground of the worke: also to seeke dimensions of heights, bredths, &c. by protracting after my new kinde of working, to separate or inclose grounds, or make any figure according vnto any proportion assigned onely by the staffe, to metamorphize or transforme any figure from one shape vnto any other, for the more speede in measuring to finde what proportion peeces of ground, glasse, boords, or any superficies one hath to the other: the making of a compendious Table to containe the legall part of measuring ground, with many Apophthegmes, requisite for all Geodetors to vnderstand.

    _ THE SECOND PART OF Geodetia, containing the measuring of the superficiall content or Area of any platte, peece of ground, mappe or such like, howsoeuer formed: and that two kinde of waies, as Arithmeticall, or vulgarly without calculation, with diuerse new tables, as well for the casting vp or deuiding of grounds, as also to extract the square roote, or finde the true square of any number, with the measuring of all kinde of superficies, as boords, glasse, &c. or solids, as tymber, stone, &c. after diuerse waies, both old & new, together with the ground of the worke: also to seeke dimensions of heights, bredths, &c. by protracting after my new kinde of working, to separate or inclose grounds, or make any figure according vnto any proportion assigned onely by the staffe, to metamorphize or transforme any figure from one shape vnto any other, for the more speede in measuring to finde what proportion peeces of ground, glasse, boords, or any superficies one hath to the other: the making of a compendious Table to containe the legall part of measuring ground, with many Apophthegmes, requisite for all Geodetors to vnderstand.

    _ THE SECOND PART OF Geodetia, containing the measuring of the superficiall content or Area of any platte, peece of ground, mappe or such like, howsoeuer formed: and that two kinde of waies, as Arithmeticall, or vulgarly without calculation, with diuerse new tables, as well for the casting vp or deuiding of grounds, as also to extract the square roote, or finde the true square of any number, with the measuring of all kinde of superficies, as boords, glasse, &c. or solids, as tymber, stone, &c. after diuerse waies, both old & new, together with the ground of the worke: also to seeke dimensions of heights, bredths, &c. by protracting after my new kinde of working, to separate or inclose grounds, or make any figure according vnto any proportion assigned onely by the staffe, to metamorphize or transforme any figure from one shape vnto any other, for the more speede in measuring to finde what proportion peeces of ground, glasse, boords, or any superficies one hath to the other: the making of a compendious Table to containe the legall part of measuring ground, with many Apophthegmes, requisite for all Geodetors to vnderstand.

    _ THE SECOND PART OF Geodetia, containing the measuring of the superficiall content or Area of any platte, peece of ground, mappe or such like, howsoeuer formed: and that two kinde of waies, as Arithmeticall, or vulgarly without calculation, with diuerse new tables, as well for the casting vp or deuiding of grounds, as also to extract the square roote, or finde the true square of any number, with the measuring of all kinde of superficies, as boords, glasse, &c. or solids, as tymber, stone, &c. after diuerse waies, both old & new, together with the ground of the worke: also to seeke dimensions of heights, bredths, &c. by protracting after my new kinde of working, to separate or inclose grounds, or make any figure according vnto any proportion assigned onely by the staffe, to metamorphize or transforme any figure from one shape vnto any other, for the more speede in measuring to finde what proportion peeces of ground, glasse, boords, or any superficies one hath to the other: the making of a compendious Table to containe the legall part of measuring ground, with many Apophthegmes, requisite for all Geodetors to vnderstand.

    _ THE SECOND PART OF Geodetia, containing the measuring of the superficiall content or Area of any platte, peece of ground, mappe or such like, howsoeuer formed: and that two kinde of waies, as Arithmeticall, or vulgarly without calculation, with diuerse new tables, as well for the casting vp or deuiding of grounds, as also to extract the square roote, or finde the true square of any number, with the measuring of all kinde of superficies, as boords, glasse, &c. or solids, as tymber, stone, &c. after diuerse waies, both old & new, together with the ground of the worke: also to seeke dimensions of heights, bredths, &c. by protracting after my new kinde of working, to separate or inclose grounds, or make any figure according vnto any proportion assigned onely by the staffe, to metamorphize or transforme any figure from one shape vnto any other, for the more speede in measuring to finde what proportion peeces of ground, glasse, boords, or any superficies one hath to the other: the making of a compendious Table to containe the legall part of measuring ground, with many Apophthegmes, requisite for all Geodetors to vnderstand.

    _ THE SECOND PART OF Geodetia, containing the measuring of the superficiall content or Area of any platte, peece of ground, mappe or such like, howsoeuer formed: and that two kinde of waies, as Arithmeticall, or vulgarly without calculation, with diuerse new tables, as well for the casting vp or deuiding of grounds, as also to extract the square roote, or finde the true square of any number, with the measuring of all kinde of superficies, as boords, glasse, &c. or solids, as tymber, stone, &c. after diuerse waies, both old & new, together with the ground of the worke: also to seeke dimensions of heights, bredths, &c. by protracting after my new kinde of working, to separate or inclose grounds, or make any figure according vnto any proportion assigned onely by the staffe, to metamorphize or transforme any figure from one shape vnto any other, for the more speede in measuring to finde what proportion peeces of ground, glasse, boords, or any superficies one hath to the other: the making of a compendious Table to containe the legall part of measuring ground, with many Apophthegmes, requisite for all Geodetors to vnderstand.

    _ THE SECOND PART OF Geodetia, containing the measuring of the superficiall content or Area of any platte, peece of ground, mappe or such like, howsoeuer formed: and that two kinde of waies, as Arithmeticall, or vulgarly without calculation, with diuerse new tables, as well for the casting vp or deuiding of grounds, as also to extract the square roote, or finde the true square of any number, with the measuring of all kinde of superficies, as boords, glasse, &c. or solids, as tymber, stone, &c. after diuerse waies, both old & new, together with the ground of the worke: also to seeke dimensions of heights, bredths, &c. by protracting after my new kinde of working, to separate or inclose grounds, or make any figure according vnto any proportion assigned onely by the staffe, to metamorphize or transforme any figure from one shape vnto any other, for the more speede in measuring to finde what proportion peeces of ground, glasse, boords, or any superficies one hath to the other: the making of a compendious Table to containe the legall part of measuring ground, with many Apophthegmes, requisite for all Geodetors to vnderstand.
